INTRO:
This is a python client for 'gabriel-proxy-mirror.py' proxy server (gabriel/server/bin/gabriel-proxy-dummy). 
IMPORTANT: set flag ANDROID_CLIENT to False in 'gabriel-proxy-mirror.py'

Python client streams camera feed to the backend. gabriel-proxy-mirror transform the origin image into a mirrored one along y-axis, and then transmit the image (in json) back to the client.


USAGE:
gui version:
./ui.py

command line version:
./client.py

Dependency:
opencv: sudo apt-get install libopencv-dev python-opencv

For gui version, you'll also need pyQt:
sudo apt-get install python-qt4

INSTALLATION:
Create a virtualenv and install the requirements listed in requirements.txt.
virtualenv --python=python2.7 ./venv
. ./venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
